This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of the storage manager component of a database system, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). The proposed strategy involves optimizing the I/O throughput, which is a key aspect of data structures and algorithms, falling under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The evaluation of the storage manager over different storage devices, including a solid-state drive, involves understanding the underlying operating system and storage architecture, which falls under cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper also discusses the coordination of multiple queries, which is a topic in the field of cs.AR (Architecture), and the proposed strategy involves implementing a cache layer and eviction mechanism, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
